View.html.title: View
View.html.name: View
View.html.description: View - the base view for handlng display in the MV* Concept

View.html#permissions.title: permissions
View.html#permissions.name: permissions
View.html#permissions.description: Sets the permissions to the view

View.html#remove.title: remove()
View.html#remove.name: remove
View.html#remove.description: Remove the view and all binds

View.html#setElement.title: setElement()
View.html#setElement.name: setElement
View.html#setElement.description: Change the view's element (this.el property) and re-delegate the view's events on the new element.

View.html#delegateEvents.title: delegateEvents()
View.html#delegateEvents.name: delegateEvents
View.html#delegateEvents.description: Creates the this.el and this.$el references for this view using the given el. el can be a CSS selector or an HTML string, a jQuery context or an element. Subclasses can override this to utilize an alternative DOM manipulation API and are only required to set the this.el property. Set callbacks, where this.events is a hash of pairs. Callbacks will be bound to the view, with this set properly. Uses event delegation for efficiency. Omitting the selector binds the event to this._el.

View.html#delegate.title: delegate()
View.html#delegate.name: delegate
View.html#delegate.description: Add a single event listener to the view's element (or a child element using selector). This only works for delegate-able events: not focus, blur, and not change, submit, and reset in Internet Explorer.

View.html#undelegateEvents.title: undelegateEvents()
View.html#undelegateEvents.name: undelegateEvents
View.html#undelegateEvents.description: Clears all callbacks previously bound to the view by delegateEvents. You usually don't need to use this, but may wish to if you have multiple views attached to the same DOM element.

View.html#undelegate.title: undelegate()
View.html#undelegate.name: undelegate
View.html#undelegate.description: A finer-grained undelegateEvents for removing a single delegated event. selector and listener are both optional.

View.html#addPermission.title: addPermission( permission, negative )
View.html#addPermission.name: addPermission
View.html#addPermission.description: Adds a permission to the view

View.html#removePermission.title: removePermission( permission, negative )
View.html#removePermission.name: removePermission
View.html#removePermission.description: Removes a permission to the view

View.html#clearPermissions.title: clearPermissions()
View.html#clearPermissions.name: clearPermissions
View.html#clearPermissions.description: Clears the permissions in the view

View.html#matchesPermission.title: matchesPermission( match, negative )
View.html#matchesPermission.name: matchesPermission
View.html#matchesPermission.description: Matches a permission in the view

View.html#canDisplay.title: canDisplay()
View.html#canDisplay.name: canDisplay
View.html#canDisplay.description: Callback to return if this view can display
